e\nlevel for super-stall loads gives results which are in agreement with\nexperimental data. Our analysis suggests that the load-dependent detachment of\na dynein in a team is qualitatively different at sub-stall and super-stall\nloads, a conclusion which is likely to have implications in other situations\ninvolving collective effects of many motors.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Sat, 26 May 2012 07:51:39 GMT"}],"update_date":"2015-06-05"}
