{"id":"1205.5883","submitter":"Victor Afonso","authors":"Diego Julio Cirilo-Lombardo","title":"Geometrical properties of Riemannian superspaces, observables and\n  physical states","comments":"16 pags. 3 figures. To Anna Grigorievna Kartavenko and Academic\n  Professor Alexei Norianovich Sissakian, in memoriam","journal-ref":null,"doi":"10.1140/epjc/s10052-012-2079-x","report-no":null,"categories":"hep-th gr-qc","license":"http://arxiv.org/licenses/nonexclusive-distrib/1.0/","abstract":"  Classical and quantum aspects of physical systems that can be described by\nRiemannian non degenerate superspaces are analyzed from the topological and\ngeometrical points of view. For the N=1 case the simplest supermetric\nintroduced in [Physics Letters B \\textbf{661}, (2008),186] have the correct\nnumber of degrees of freedom for the fermion fields and the super-momentum\nfulfil the mass shell condition, in sharp contrast with other cases in the\nliterature where the supermetric is degenerate. This fact leads a deviation of\nthe 4-impulse (e.g. mass constraint) that can be mechanically interpreted as a\nmodification of the Newton's law. Quantum aspects of the physical states and\nthe basic states and the projection relation between them, are completely\ndescribed due the introduction of a new Majorana-Weyl representation of the\ngenerators of the underlying group manifold. A new oscillatory fermionic effect\nin the $B_{0}$ part of the vaccum solution involving the chiral and antichiral\ncomponents of this Majorana bispinor is explicitly shown.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Sat, 26 May 2012 13:30:01 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Wed, 11 Jul 2012 14:34:47 GMT"}],"update_date":"2015-06-05"}
{"id":"1205.5884","submitter":"Jae Dong Noh","authors":"Pyoung-Seop Shim, Hyun Keun Lee, Jae Dong Noh","title":"Percolation transitions with nonlocal constraint","comments":"4 pages, 5 figures","journal-ref":"Phys. Rev. E 86, 031113 (2012)","doi":"10.1103/PhysRevE.86.031113","report-no":null,"categories":"cond-mat.stat-mech","license":"http://arxiv.org/licenses/nonexclusive-distrib/1.0/","abstract":"  We investigate percolation transitions in a nonlocal network model\nnumerically. In this model, each node has an exclusive partner and a link is\nforbidden between two nodes whose $r$-neighbors share any exclusive pair. The\n$r$-neighbor of a node $x$ is defined as a set of at most $N^r$ neighbors of\n$x$, where $N$ is the total number of nodes. The parameter $r$ controls the\nstrength of a nonlocal effect. The system is found to undergo a percolation\ntransition belonging to the mean field universality class for $r< 1/2$. On the\nother hand, for $r>1/2$, the system undergoes a peculiar phase transition from\na non-percolating phase to a quasi-critical phase where the largest cluster\nsize $G$ scales as $G \\sim N^{\\alpha}$ with $\\alpha = 0.74 (1)$. In the\nmarginal case with $r=1/2$, the model displays a percolation transition that\ndoes not belong to the mean field universality class.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Sat, 26 May 2012 13:38:48 GMT"}],"update_date":"2012-10-09"}
